In 2004, Google formed its non-profit philanthropic wing [[Google.org]], giving it a starting fund of $1 billion. The express mission of the organization is to help with the issues of [[climate change]] (see also [[global warming]] and [[climate change denial]]), global public health, and [[global poverty]].
